# Required Perl Modules
Email::Send::Gmail (If using gmail)  ->  command: sudo cpan install Email::Send::Gmail
MIME::Lite         (if using email)  ->  command: sudo cpan install MIME:Lite

#Install

# Feel free to test. All data manipulation is done by snapraid http://www.snapraid.it/
1. sudo apt-get install git
2. git clone https://github.com/SmileyMan/snapPERL.git
3. You can of course run as a root crontab. Be happy it does what you need first.

#### For stable release don't follow yet ####
(Run as root so recommend script placed in root home)
1. sudo apt-get install git
2. sudo -i
3. git clone https://github.com/SmileyMan/snapPERL.git
4. cd snapPERL
5. gedit/vi/nano Config (Modify setting to suit)
6. ./snapPERL.pl to confirm all runs ok
7. crontab -e
add 
    0 2 * * * ~/snapPERL/snapPERL.pl >/dev/null 2>&1 
to crontab and save (Run at 2am each day adjust as needed)
8. exit

If using email
1. sudo cpan install Email::Send::Gmail (If using gmail)
2. sudo cpan install MIME:Lite (If using email)
 
